sentences.english: The decay must be cleaned out and the cavity filled by a dentist.
sentences.chinese: 必須由牙科醫生把齲壞清理乾淨並充填。

sentences.english: I have to make an appointment to get braces for Dorothy's teeth.
sentences.chinese: 我現在還得去牙科醫生那兒給多蘿西裝一副矯牙套。

sentences.english: The word “dentist”denotes a doctor whose work is the care of teeth.
sentences.chinese: “牙科醫生”一詞意謂其工作是醫治牙齒的醫生。

sentences.english: The dentist sequesters the tooth he is working on.
sentences.chinese: 牙科醫生把他正研究的牙齒隔開了。
這是牙科醫生用的鑽子。

sentences.english: They say there's a lotta dentists staying here.
sentences.chinese: 他們說有許多牙科醫生住在這裏。

sentences.english: If in doubt ask your dentist.
sentences.chinese: 若有任何疑問請諮詢牙科醫生。

sentences.english: I told my dentist my teeth are going yellow. He told me to wear a brown necktie.
sentences.chinese: 我跟牙科醫生說我的牙齒有點黃，他叫我戴褐色領帶。

sentences.english: An American dentist would die seeing this.
sentences.chinese: 美國牙科醫生看到這些會被嚇死的。
牙科醫生則是完全中性。

sentences.english: Mouth guards customized by a dentist can be useful yet pricey.
sentences.chinese: 牙科醫生量身定製的嘴護套是有用的，但是價格昂貴。

sentences.english: The dentist extracted her wisdom tooth.
sentences.chinese: 牙科醫生將她的智牙拔出。

sentences.english: The dentist extracted her wisdom teeth.
sentences.chinese: 牙科醫生將她的智牙拔出。

sentences.english: I have gone to the dentist to extract the bad tooth.
sentences.chinese: 我已到牙科醫生那裏把壞牙拔掉了。
